+{"id":"frankenpandas-1zzp","title":"[EPIC] Row MultiIndex — full DataFrame row-axis integration","description":"Genuine row MultiIndex support on DataFrame. Scope (tracked here as an umbrella; file child beads per slice):\n\n  1. DataFrame row axis: promote DataFrame::index from Index<IndexLabel> to an enum-or-generic over {Index, MultiIndex<Vec<IndexLabel>>} so row-axis tuple keys round-trip instead of being flattened to Utf8('a|1').\n\n  2. GroupBy multi-key output: groupby([k1, k2]).sum() / .mean() / etc. currently emit string-flattened index keys (s:a|i:1 per FP-P2C-005, FP-P2C-011). Emit real (k1, k2) tuple-keyed row MultiIndex instead; strip the flatten sep codepath.\n\n  3. Indexing: .loc[(a, 1)] tuple-key indexing; .loc[idx[('a', :)]] level-slicing; .xs(key, level=N); .get_loc((a, 1)).\n\n  4. Reshape round-trips: set_index([c1, c2]) / reset_index() pair that actually round-trips through a row MultiIndex (currently scaffolded); stack / unstack that lift/drop a row-level; swaplevel / reorder_levels on row axis.\n\n  5. IO: Excel/CSV/Parquet/Feather write emit multi-row header + left-index block; read reverses the pattern (index_col=[c1, c2]).\n\n  6. Live oracle coverage: packet fixtures for each of the above against the pandas oracle.\n\nBlocker for diic-family credibility: the README now honestly says 'Row MultiIndex: Scaffolded' (commit-pending, br-0yz7). Closing that qualifier requires this epic landing.\n\nSuggested decomposition strategy: (1) is the foundation — pick between (a) enum Index<Flat|Multi> behind a trait, or (b) generic DataFrame<Idx: IndexLike>. (2)-(6) then unblock incrementally behind (1). Each slice wants its own child bead so progress is trackable.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-22T11:40:44.867811975Z","created_by":"cc-pandas","updated_at":"2026-04-22T11:40:44.867811975Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","multi-index","row-index"]}
